# Project Structure Rules

## Monorepo Layout
- `/client` — React + Vite frontend
- `/server` — Express + Prisma backend
- Never put feature code in the repo root. Root-level files are config only.

## Client Structure
```
client/src/
├── assets/          # Static images, fonts, icons
├── components/
│   ├── ui/          # Base primitives: Button, Card, Input, etc.
│   └── layout/      # Header, Footer, PageWrapper
├── features/        # Feature-scoped folders
│   └── menu/
│       ├── components/
│       ├── hooks/
│       └── types.ts
├── hooks/           # Shared custom hooks
├── lib/             # API client, query client
├── pages/           # Route-level page components
├── routes/          # React Router config
├── store/           # Zustand stores
├── styles/          # Global CSS, Tailwind base
└── types/           # Shared TypeScript types
```

## Server Structure
```
server/src/
├── config/          # env.ts — only place process.env is read
├── lib/             # prisma.ts singleton
├── middleware/      # errorHandler, logger, validate, auth placeholder
└── modules/
    └── menu/        # menu.router, menu.controller, menu.service, menu.schema
```

## Barrel Exports
- Every `components/`, `features/`, and `modules/` subfolder must have an `index.ts` that re-exports its public API.
- Import from the folder, not the file: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui'` not `'@/components/ui/button'`.

## Shared Types
- `client/src/types/` holds types shared across the frontend.
- Design them to be extractable into a shared package later (no browser or Node-specific imports).
